<refnamediv>
  <refname>stg-diff</refname>
  <refpurpose>Show the tree diff</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv id="_synopsis">
<blockquote>
<literallayout><emphasis>stg</emphasis> diff [options] [--] [&lt;files or dirs&gt;]</literallayout>
</blockquote>
</refsynopsisdiv>
<refsect1 id="_description">
<title>DESCRIPTION</title>
<simpara>Show the diff (default) or diffstat between the current working copy
or a tree-ish object and another tree-ish object (defaulting to HEAD).
File names can also be given to restrict the diff output. The
tree-ish object has the format accepted by the <citerefentry>
  <refentrytitle>stg-id</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum>
</citerefentry> command.</simpara>
</refsect1>
<refsect1 id="_options">
<title>OPTIONS</title>
<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term>
-r rev1[..[rev2]]
</term>
<term>
--range rev1[..[rev2]]
</term>
<listitem>
<simpara>
        Show the diff between revisions.
</simpara>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>
-s
</term>
<term>
--stat
</term>
<listitem>
<simpara>
        Show the stat instead of the diff.
</simpara>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>
-O OPTIONS
</term>
<term>
--diff-opts OPTIONS
</term>
<listitem>
<simpara>
        Extra options to pass to "git diff".
</simpara>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</refsect1>
